The birds of the Esquiline are the crows that fed on the bodies of slaves, criminals and destitute persons flung there unburied or only half-covered with earth. In Sat. 1. 8. ro Horace says of the Esquiline miserae plebi stabat commune sepulcrum. Maecenas converted part of

the hill into a garden, but the ground outside the garden was still covered with bones (ibid. p. αα).
